CatDescriptText: Martha Tyson, owner, Tyson's Bakery, was part of the Pittsburgher's Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 5, 1959 with question: "Do you believe Allegheny County Democrats and Republicans have selected their best candidates for public offices in past 10 years?"  Answer reads: "There have been good candidates on both sides, and then there have been some on both sides who were not so good."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Martha Tyson wearing light colored blouse with rolled sleeves, standing at glass counter in Tyson's Bakery, Centre Avenue, Hill District
